{
  "name": "OpenCloud \u2014 End-to-end smoke test",
  "meta": {
    "description": "**Opt-in live integration test.** Exercises every OpenCloud node operation against a real OpenCloud server. The repo test suite uses mocked HTTP via nock and runs in CI; this workflow is for manual end-to-end verification.\n\nBefore running:\n  1. Create an OpenCloud credential in n8n (Settings \u2192 Credentials). For local Docker dev, the typical URL is https://host.docker.internal:9200.\n  2. Patch this workflow with your credential id:\n       ./examples/apply-credentials.sh <credential-id> > /tmp/smoke.json\n     and import /tmp/smoke.json. Or import as-is and pick the credential on every node manually.\n\nNo drive id needed \u2014 the Resolve-space step calls /graph/v1.0/me/drives via the Space:List operation and the Config Code node picks the personal drive automatically. Works against any backend.\n\nWhat it does (in order):\n  0. Cleanup any pre-existing /n8n-smoke from a prior run (idempotent re-runs)\n  1. Create /n8n-smoke folder\n  2. Generate test bytes\n  3. Upload as /n8n-smoke/hello.txt\n  4. List /n8n-smoke\n  5. Download /n8n-smoke/hello.txt\n  6. Create /n8n-smoke/archive subfolder\n  7. Copy hello.txt \u2192 archive/copy.txt\n  8. Move archive/copy.txt \u2192 archive/renamed.txt\n  9. Create a public share link for hello.txt\n 10. Delete hello.txt\n 11. Delete /n8n-smoke (cleanup)\n\nEach OpenCloud node has continueOnFail=true so a failure in one step does not break the rest. Step 12 (Verify results) aggregates errors and prints actionable detail (e.g. password-policy hints)."
  },
